This script runs simulations with the most up-to-date functions

Define parameters

fire <- "AMRC"
years <- 20
cumsum_2015 <- 0.441
cumsum_2016 <- 0.912
cumsum_2017 <- 1
iterations <- 500
max_shrub_ht_cm <- 250
max_shrub_ht_years <- 15
n_seedlings <- 100
length_m <- 40
height_m <- 40
lambda <- 4
shrub_clumpiness <- 7

  tm_borders(col = "black", lwd= 5)+

  tm_raster(col = "sqrt_shrubarea3", title = "Shrub competition index", palette = "Greys", alpha = .5)+

  tm_raster(col = "ShrubSpp03", alpha = .7, title = "Shrub species", palette = "Pastel1")+

  tm_symbols(size = "Pine height (cm)", col = "#DCC960", size.max = 300, border.lwd = 3)+
tm_shape(pts.sf.abco.graph)+
  tm_symbols(size = "Fir height (cm)", col = "#899DA4", size.max = 300, border.lwd = 3)

It is recommended to set size.max to at least 525.763809723925. Another option is to set size.lim = c(0, 300), which truncates the size of the 11 larger symbols. Use the scale argument to increase the size of all symbols.

Height by year

dfsimallreps_summary <- dfsimallreps %>% 
  ungroup() %>%
  mutate(rep = as.factor(paste(rep))) %>% 
  group_by(rep, Years, Species) %>% 
  mutate(mean_ht_years = mean(Ht_cm1))
dfsimallreps_summary %>% dplyr::select(rep, Years, mean_ht_years) %>% summary()
## Adding missing grouping variables: `Species`
##  Species            rep              Years       mean_ht_years   
##  ABCO:890692   42     :   3158   Min.   : 9.00   Min.   : 33.51  
##  PIPO:539113   283    :   3132   1st Qu.:12.00   1st Qu.: 71.14  
##                298    :   3116   Median :16.00   Median :110.91

ggplot(dfsimallreps_summary, aes(x = as.factor(Years), y = mean_ht_years, fill = Species, col = Species))+
  geom_boxplot(alpha = .2, outlier.alpha = .02)+
  geom_smooth(aes(x = as.factor(Years), y = mean_ht_years, group = Species, col = Species), size = 1)+
  ggtitle("Results for 1000 simulations")+
  xlab("Years since fire")+
  ylab("Average tree ht (cm) by simulation")+
  theme_bw()+
  scale_color_manual(values = c("#899DA4", "#9A8822"), labels = c("Fir", "Pine"))+
  scale_fill_manual(values = c("#899DA4", "#9A8822"), labels = c("Fir", "Pine"))+
  theme(text = element_text(size = 16), 
        panel.grid.minor.x = element_blank(),

Next steps to improve the model

  1. Use Kristens data or Hughs data for initial conditions
  2. Improve dispersal kernel based on Kristen/Hughs data
  3. Include residual surviving trees and their seed dispersal
  4. Include seed dispersal of post-fire regen once it reaches reproductive age
  5. Add customization of patch size and shape
  6. Add customization of whether the weather conditions reflect those of 2015, 2016, or 2017
  7. Change sapling growth equations once they emerge from the shrub canopy

  1. Update display of shrub competition after simulation years
  2. Add 0/1 for emergent year = when 50% of trees are above shrub canopy
  3. apply to King, American River Complex, rest of the fires I measured
